{{spoiler|[[Living World Season 3]]}} {{Location infobox | levels = 80 | type = Zone | requires = lws3 | within = Heart of Maguuma | location tree = Tyria; Heart of Maguuma | id = 1165 | region id = 10 | continent id = 1 | map = Bloodstone Fen level 2 map.jpg }} [[File:Bloodstone Fen level 3 map.jpg|thumb|240px|Sky (level 3) map]] [[File:Bloodstone Fen level 1 map.jpg|thumb|240px|Underground (level 1) map]] [[Bloodstone Fen]] is a [[zone]] available via [[Living World Season 3]] episode [[Out of the Shadows]]. Found in the [[Heart of Maguuma]], it is the location of the [[Maguuma Jungle]] [[Bloodstone]]. The [[White Mantle]] has been active here since their exile from [[Kryta]], studying the Bloodstone's properties and how to harness its power. Years of tampering with the Bloodstone has caused it to explode, devastating the surrounding area and leaving orbs of [[Unbound Magic]] and pockets of [[Unstable Magic]] suspended in the air.
The majority of the [[White Mantle]] and [[Pact]] personnel who survived the explosion have been driven mad, hungering for Bloodstone magic. The souls of humans sacrificed atop the Bloodstone have been freed and haunt the area as restless spirits, most notably the dangerous [[Ghostly Justiciar Hablion|Justiciar Hablion]]. The White Mantle have also managed to take control of [[jade construct]]s, which are periodically brought into Bloodstone Maw to gather any lingering energy.
While in Bloodstone Fen, characters have access to special skills usable while [[gliding]], channeling ambient magic to attack foes and maneuver while airborne.
== Getting there == Like most of the Living World Season 3 zones, Bloodstone Fen is not directly connected to neighboring areas. In order to reach it, one can use one of the following methods:
* Complete the [[Out of the Shadows]] instance [[Research in Rata Novus]] - the second story step of Episode 1 from [[Living World Season 3]]. * Use a [[Bloodstone Fen Portal Scroll]]. * Use a [[Teleport to Friend]] after having unlocked the [[Out of the Shadows]] episode on the account. ** Not having unlocked the story episode will result in a wasted Teleport to Friend. *** If your friend is actually standing on the waypoint, you will get the waypoint, but you will still not have access to the map until starting the episode.
== Map resources == * {{item icon|Unbound Magic}} is found throughout the map and is dropped by various enemies and events. * {{item icon|Blood Ruby|Blood Rubies}} can be found in [[Bloodstone Crystals|Bloodstone Crystal]] ore nodes throughout the map and as event rewards. These are needed to buy Blood Ruby accessories from [[Scholar Rakka]].
== Completion rewards == * {{exp|8001}} * {{rewards item|Unbound Magic|qty=100}} * {{rewards item|Blood Ruby|qty=5}} * 1 piece of [[gear]] of {{rarity|Rare}} or higher [[Item#Rarity|rarity]]. * One of the following: ** {{rewards item|Transmutation Charge (item)|chance=chance}} ** {{rewards item|Black Lion Key|chance=chance}} (rare)
== Gliding skills == Initially, characters can only use [[Focused Magic]]. To unlock the other skills, they must be purchased from [[Natto]] aboard the [[Pride of the Pact]] airship. The purchase is for all characters and is only required once per account.
